            <div class="projects" id="proj-start">
                <h1>Projects</h1> 
                <section class='proj'>
                    <dl>

                        <dt>Simple Animator</dt>
                        <label>Java</label>
                        <dd><h4><a href="https://github.com/AndrewLucia/Northeastern-Projects/tree/master/hw06(3)" target="alt">Github</a></h4></dd>
                        <dd>This is a simple animator which allows you to create certain shapes and transform them at certain times to create a simple animation. 
                            It offers different views including an SVG, a Visual, and a Textual. It utilizes the MVC pattern.</dd>

                        <dt>BGP Router</dt>
                        <label>Python</label>
                        <dd><h4><a href="https://github.com/AndrewLucia/Northeastern-Projects/blob/master/router.py" target="alt">Github</a></h4></dd>
                        <dd>A simple BGP router that handles routing packets, updating, coallescing and other router functions.
                            "Packets" are JSON entries of a specific format depending on the packet.</dd>
                        
                        <dt>TCP Implementation</dt>
                        <label>Python</label>
                        <dd><h4><a href="https://github.com/AndrewLucia/Northeastern-Projects/tree/master/TCP%20Implementation" target="alt">Github</a></h4></dd>
                        <dd>Two files that represent a sender and receiver utilizing a simple implementation of TCP in Python.
                            The implementation uses a version of slow-start and resend to handle congestion, drops, etc.
                        </dd>

                        <dt>Memory Allocator</dt>
                        <label>C</label>
                        <dd><h4><a href="https://github.com/AndrewLucia/Northeastern-Projects/tree/master/Simple%20Memory%20Allocator" target="alt">Github</a></h4></dd>
                        <dd>This is an interpretation of the C function malloc. It uses mmap to allocate the memory pages
                            and uses an implementation of the bucket linked list structure to keep track and free memory blocks.</dd>
                        
                        <dt>File System</dt>
                        <label>C</label>
                        <dd><h4><a href="https://github.com/AndrewLucia/Northeastern-Projects/tree/master/File%20System" target="alt">Github</a></h4></dd>
                        <dd>A working file system that uses a linked list of nodes containing meta-data to keep track of memory.
                            Contains everything from making, renaming, removing directories and more.
                        </dd>

                    </dl>
                </section>
